g.text: Logic: Klaasje's hidden documents -- from the empty buoy.
Oranjese Passport: The woman on the photo does not reply. She looks at you with mysterious eyes, disguised as someone else.
Encyclopedia: A curious octopus sometimes collects things? Or a cuttlefish?
Cuno: "Cuno's gonna say it's *not* any of the things you *think* it is. Cuno'd have to get deep into this shit, but whatever it is -- you got played here. That's for sure."
Oranjese Passport: And not *Annouk Meijer-Smit*. Like she told you. Annouk -- Meijer -- Smit. Remember? You got lied to. Again.
Shivers: The winds are silent. The streets are empty of her. She is no longer in the city of Revachol.
Savoir Faire: Precinct 57 needs to double the security around her.
Encyclopedia: A curious octopus would do something similar. Or even a cuttlefish.
Drama: This Katarzine Alasije -- it's safe to say it's not her either. In short: you got lied to, sire. Good luck to whoever is questioning her in the 57th right now.
You: "The phasmid took it -- and I *sensed* it do so. I saw something open up the buoy with spindly legs." (Point to your head.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "Perhaps... But that still doesn't explain how it got into the nest."
Kim Kitsuragi: He opens his notes. "She said it would be for *Annouk Meijer-Smit*. Annouk -- Meijer -- Smit."
You: "Perhaps it had a vendetta against our Miss Oranje?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "An octopus belongs to a very different Class. It's not even an insect, it's a mollusc. But, yes -- I see your point."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No. She lied to us. Her so-called real name was not her real name. Somehow she's managed to lie to us about that too..." He almost smiles.
You: "Maybe this is her real passport? Not a fake? Because this is her real name."
Volition: I told you she kept on lying to you. She's probably lying to someone else right now -- another detective.
Rhetoric: By now, the lieutenant has accepted your unusual methods.
Jump to: [Cuno: ""Cool. Got lied to. Double-lied to...."]
Cuno: "Cool. Got lied to. Double-lied to. I get it. You cops need the Cuno on stuff like this. No one lies to the Cuno." He nods, with a stern and serious expression.
Reaction Speed: She said the false passport would be for *Annouk Meijer-Smit*...
Volition: I told you she kept on lying to you. She's probably lying to someone else right now -- another detective.
Empathy: Would it? Maybe it was simply curious.
Volition: I told you she kept lying to you. She's probably lying to someone else right now. In another city.
Logic: Katarzine Alasije was supposed to be her *real* name. Where *Klaasje* comes from, remember? God dammit!
Kim Kitsuragi: "Like a magpie?" He looks around. "What a coincidence. Then it would also have *collected* the other objects, which would be highly unusual..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Like a magpie?" He looks around. "What a coincidence. Then it would also have *collected* the other objects, which would be highly unusual..."
Oranjese Passport: It's Klaasje. With short, black hair and glasses. She looks boyish, younger somehow.

Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know who Katarzine Alasije is, but it's safe to say it's not her either. In short: we got lied to, again. In a way she's *still* lying to us..." The lieutenant can't help but smile.
Drama: This Katarzine Alasije -- it's safe to say it's not her either. In short: you got lied to, sire. Maybe it's best we let her go -- at least we don't have to question her again.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Maybe our man, Mr. Dros, took it from Klaasje's -- or whatever her name was -- hiding place? Or..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Klaasje's hidden documents..." The lieutenant looks at it in your hands. "From the empty buoy."
You: "What was this doing in the phasmid's nest?"
Volition: I told you she kept lying to you. She's probably lying to someone else right now. In another city. She moves fast.
You: "Katarzine Alasije was supposed to be her real name. She lied to us."
Oranjese Passport: This passport, issued by the Sovereign Republic of Oranje -- is issued to a black haired woman called Katarzine Alasije.
Volition: I told you she kept lying to you. She's probably lying to someone else right now. In another city. She moves fast.
Oranjese Passport: The girl on the passport looks at you with no answer. She is not Katarzine Alasije. Or Annouk Meijer-Smit. *Or* Klaasje. That much is sure.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, somehow she managed to lie to us -- *one more time*. In a way she's still lying to us right now." The lieutenant smiles.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know who Katarzine Alasije is, but it's safe to say it's not her either. In short: we got lied to, again. Good luck to whoever is questioning her in the 57th right now."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know. But it's not Katarzine Alasije. Or Klaasje. Or Annouk Meijer-Smit. We didn't even scratch the surface with her, detective."
You: "It's not the name she said would be on here. I got lied to."
You: "She told me it was her real name -- and it isn't this. It isn't even the name she said would be on here..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I can see how the helmet could wash up on the island. And the scope -- maybe Mr. Dros lost it? But to seek this out would be *very* unusual behaviour for an arthropod."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Phasmids are not capable of holding grudges. Only humans and some tracking predators do that."
Kim Kitsuragi: He looks east. "Perhaps it's better that we didn't arrest her. Who knows what hell she'd be raising in my district by now..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Klaasje's hidden documents..." The lieutenant looks at it in your hands. "That she said would be in a buoy on the coast."

Cuno: "Yeah -- okay. *Don't* loop Cuno in. Leave the Cuno in the dark. Fine." He pretends he doesn't care.
Empathy: An old photo. Before life came and did what it does.

Logic: Even worse -- *Katarzine Alasije* was supposed to be her *real* name. Where *Klaasje* comes from, remember? God dammit!

Cuno: "Okay. So what? Loop Cuno in on this."
You: "Perhaps it was curious? Like an octopus?"
Logic: Klaasje's hidden documents. That she said would be in a buoy on the coast.
Cuno: "Fuck if I know... maybe it's collecting shit? Like an octopus can get, like, curious?"
